SIMPLE: filariasis
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Filariasis
<hw>Fil`a*ri"a*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool., Med.)</fld> <def>the presence of filariae
within the body of an organism; infection with filariae. It is mostly
found in tropical and subtropical regions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>a disease caused by nematodes in
the blood or tissues of the body causing blockage of lymphatic vessels.
Death of the adult worms may lead to inflammation and permanent
fibrosis; the condition may lead to serious symptoms, such as
elephantiasis or blindness. See <er>river blindness</er></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>filariid</ent>⟦br⟧
